## 1. PingOne OAuth 2.0 / OIDC

### Pattern: Always BFF (Backend For Frontend)

The `banking_api_server` is the confidential OAuth client. It holds tokens in `req.session.oauthTokens`. The React SPA never sees raw tokens.

```javascript
// ✅ Store tokens in session only
req.session.oauthTokens = {
  accessToken: tokens.access_token,
  refreshToken: tokens.refresh_token,
  idToken: tokens.id_token,
  expiresAt: Date.now() + ((tokens.expires_in || 3600) * 1000),
  tokenType: tokens.token_type,
};
// ❌ Never
res.json({ access_token: tokens.access_token });
```

### PingOne Endpoints

Base: `https://auth.pingone.{tld}/{envId}/as/`

| Endpoint | Use |
|---|---|
| `/as/authorize` | Start PKCE login redirect |
| `/as/token` | Exchange code, refresh, CIBA poll, client_credentials, token exchange |
| `/as/revoke` | RFC 7009 revocation |
| `/as/introspect` | RFC 7662 introspection |
| `/as/bc-authorize` | CIBA initiate |
| `/as/par` | PAR (RFC 9126) |
| `/as/device_authorization` | Device Authorization Grant |
| `/as/jwks` | Public keys for JWT verification |
| `/as/.well-known/openid-configuration` | OIDC Discovery |

Region TLDs: `com` (default) | `ca` | `eu` | `com.au` | `sg` | `asia`

Config: `const region = configStore.getEffective('pingone_region') || 'com';`

### Authorization Code + PKCE (Primary Login Flow)

```javascript
// Step 1 — Initiate login
const state        = oauthService.generateState();          // crypto.randomBytes(32).hex
const codeVerifier = oauthService.generateCodeVerifier();   // crypto.randomBytes(64).hex
const nonce        = crypto.randomBytes(16).toString('hex');

// Generate code_challenge: base64url(sha256(verifier))
function generateCodeChallenge(verifier) {
  return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(verifier).digest('base64url');
}

// Store in BOTH session AND signed PKCE cookie (Vercel cross-instance fallback)
req.session.oauthState = state;
req.session.oauthCodeVerifier = codeVerifier;
req.session.oauthNonce = nonce;
setPkceCookie(res, { state, codeVerifier, redirectUri, nonce }, isProd());

// MUST save session before redirect (async Redis store)
req.session.save(err => {
  if (err) return res.status(500).json({ error: 'session_save_failed' });
  res.redirect(authUrl);
});

// Auth URL params:
// response_type=code & client_id & redirect_uri & scope=openid profile email
// & state & code_challenge & code_challenge_method=S256 & nonce
// & acr_values (optional DaVinci policy) & login_hint (optional)
```

```javascript
// Step 2 — Callback
const pkceData = req.session.oauthState === state
  ? req.session
  : readPkceCookie(req);  // validates HMAC
if (!pkceData || pkceData.state !== state) return redirect('?error=invalid_state');

// exchangeCodeForToken uses Authorization: Basic base64(id:secret) — NOT body params
const tokens = await oauthService.exchangeCodeForToken(code, pkceData.codeVerifier, pkceData.redirectUri);

// Verify nonce to prevent replay attacks
const idTokenClaims = jwt.decode(tokens.id_token);
if (idTokenClaims.nonce !== pkceData.nonce) return redirect('?error=nonce_mismatch');
```

### Client Credentials (M2M / Agent)

```javascript
// Worker app — no refresh_token, no id_token returned
grant_type=client_credentials & client_id & client_secret (or Basic auth header)
// Use: oauthService.getAgentClientCredentialsToken()
```

### CIBA — Backchannel Authentication

```javascript
// Initiate: POST /as/bc-authorize  (Basic auth)
// login_hint=email & scope & binding_message & acr_values (optional step-up)
// Returns: { auth_req_id, expires_in, interval }

// Poll: POST /as/token
// grant_type=urn:openid:params:grant-type:ciba & auth_req_id={id}
// Errors: authorization_pending → retry; slow_down → interval += 5 (max 30); access_denied → abort; expired_token → restart
```

### Token Exchange — RFC 8693

```javascript
// T1 (user token) → T2 (MCP-scoped delegated token)
grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange
subject_token={T1} & subject_token_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token
actor_token={agentT0} & actor_token_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token  // optional
requested_token_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:access_token
audience={MCP_SERVER_AUDIENCE} & scope=banking:read banking:write

// T2 contains: sub=user.sub, act={ client_id: bff-admin-client-id }
// T1 must contain: may_act: { client_id: <adminClientId> }  (configure in PingOne token customization)
```

### Token Refresh

```javascript
// middleware/tokenRefresh.js — auto-refresh 5 min before expiry
// PingOne ROTATES refresh tokens — always store the new refresh_token
// Non-fatal: always calls next() even on error
// Enable additionalRefreshTokenReplayProtectionEnabled on the PingOne app
```

### Revocation — RFC 7009

```javascript
// On logout: revoke BOTH refresh_token AND access_token
// POST /as/revoke  token={token} & token_type_hint={hint} + client auth
// PingOne API resource tokens (api.pingone.com) cannot be revoked
```

### OIDC ID Token Validation

Validate in order: signature (RS256, JWKS) → iss → aud contains clientId → exp → nonce → acr (if step-up)

`SKIP_TOKEN_SIGNATURE_VALIDATION=true` is **fatal in production** — server exits at startup.

### PingOne App Config

| Setting | Admin | User | Agent |
|---|---|---|---|
| Type | `WEB_APP` | `WEB_APP` | `WORKER` |
| Grant types | `authorization_code`, `refresh_token`, token-exchange, CIBA | `authorization_code`, `refresh_token` | `client_credentials` |
| PKCE | `S256_REQUIRED` | `S256_REQUIRED` | N/A |
| Token auth method | `CLIENT_SECRET_BASIC` | `CLIENT_SECRET_BASIC` | `CLIENT_SECRET_BASIC` |

### Common OAuth Error Codes

| Error | Fix |
|---|---|
| `invalid_client` | Use `CLIENT_SECRET_BASIC` (Authorization header), not body params |
| `invalid_grant` | Fresh PKCE per request — never reuse codes |
| `authorization_pending` | Keep polling CIBA |
| `slow_down` | CIBA interval += 5s (max 30s) |
| `invalid_scope` | Add scope to app's resource grant in PingOne console |
| `interaction_required` | Redirect with `acr_values` |

### Security Rules

- ✅ PKCE S256 on every authorization code flow
- ✅ State + nonce validated on every callback
- ✅ Redirect URIs validated server-side (prevent open redirect)
- ✅ Tokens in server-side session only
- ✅ RFC 7009 revocation on logout (both tokens)
- ✅ `act`/`may_act` claims validated on exchanged tokens
- ✅ Scope enforcement middleware on all resource routes
- ❌ Never use implicit flow (`response_type=token`)
- ❌ Never log raw tokens
- ❌ Never expose `client_secret` to the browser

