## 4. MCP Server (TypeScript)

Located in `banking_mcp_server/`. WebSocket-based MCP protocol server.

**Core classes:**
- `BankingToolRegistry` — static registry of all tool definitions
- `BankingToolProvider` — executes tools, surfaces auth challenges
- `MCPMessageHandler` — routes `initialize` / `tools/list` / `tools/call`
- `BankingSessionManager` — per-WebSocket-connection session
- `BankingAPIClient` — calls `banking_api_server` HTTP endpoints

### Adding a New Tool

**1. Register in `BankingToolRegistry.ts`:**

```typescript
my_new_tool: {
  name: 'my_new_tool',
  description: 'Description for the AI agent',
  requiresUserAuth: true,
  requiredScopes: ['banking:transactions:write'],
  handler: 'executeMyNewTool',
  inputSchema: {
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
      account_id: { type: 'string', description: '...', minLength: 1 },
      amount:     { type: 'number', minimum: 0.01, multipleOf: 0.01 }
    },
    required: ['account_id', 'amount'],
    additionalProperties: false   // always false
  }
}
```

**2. Implement in `BankingToolProvider.ts`:**

```typescript
async executeMyNewTool(params, session, agentToken?): Promise<BankingToolResult> {
  try {
    const result = await this.apiClient.post('/api/...', params, session);
    return { type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(result, null, 2), success: true };
  } catch (err) {
    if (err instanceof AuthenticationError) {
      const challenge = await this.authChallengeHandler.generateAuthorizationChallenge(
        session.sessionId, ['banking:transactions:write']);
      return { type: 'text', text: 'Authorization required', success: false, authChallenge: challenge };
    }
    if (err instanceof BankingAPIError)
      return { type: 'text', text: `Banking error: ${err.message}`, success: false };
    throw err;
  }
}
```

### Tool Result Format

```typescript
// Always: { type: 'text', text: string, success?: boolean, error?: string, authChallenge?: AuthorizationRequest }
return { type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(data, null, 2), success: true };         // success
return { type: 'text', text: `Error: ${msg}`, success: false, error: msg };          // error
return { type: 'text', text: 'Authorization required', authChallenge: challenge };   // auth needed
```

### Deployment (NOT Vercel)

```bash
cd banking_mcp_server && npm run build:clean   # rm -rf dist && tsc
NODE_ENV=production node dist/index.js
# Required env: BANKING_API_URL, PINGONE_AUTH_URL, ADMIN_CLIENT_ID, ADMIN_CLIENT_SECRET, PORT
```

Set `MCP_SERVER_URL=wss://your-mcp-host` in Vercel project settings after deploying.

